      "writtenOn": "2021-02-01T17:39:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm. I *think* the way things are set up, this is necessary. Here\u0027s how I plan to use this in supporting the \u003cimage\u003e tag (upcoming CL soon):\n\n    switch (href.type()) {\n        case SkSVGIRI::Type::kDataURI:\n            imageAsset \u003d rp-\u003eloadImageAsset(\"\", href.iri().c_str(), \"\");\n            break;\n        case SkSVGIRI::Type::kNonlocal: {\n            const auto path \u003d SkOSPath::Dirname(href.iri().c_str());\n            const auto name \u003d SkOSPath::Basename(href.iri().c_str());\n            imageAsset \u003d rp-\u003eloadImageAsset(path.c_str(), name.c_str(), /* id */ name.c_str());\n            break;\n        }\n        default:\n            SkDebugf(\"error loading image: unhandled iri type %d\\n\", href.type());\n            return nullptr;\n    }\n\nSo really it\u0027s just so we know if we should pass the URI unmodified (including \u0027data:\u0027 prefix\u0027) or if we need to split into dirname/basename.",
